    "message_2": "To find an approximation for f(2) and f(5) using Lagrange polynomials, we will use the formula:\n\nf(x) ≈ L(x) = Σ [li(x) * f(xi)]\n\nwhere li(x) = Π [(x - xj) / (xi - xj)] for j ≠ i\n\nFirst, let's find the li(x) terms for i = 0, 1, 2, 3, and 4.\n\nl0(x) = [(x - x1)(x - x2)(x - x3)(x - x4)] / [(x0 - x1)(x0 - x2)(x0 - x3)(x0 - x4)]\n      = [(x - 1)(x - 3)(x - 4)(x - 7)] / [(0 - 1)(0 - 3)(0 - 4)(0 - 7)]\n\nl1(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x2)(x - x3)(x - x4)] / [(x1 - x0)(x1 - x2)(x1 - x3)(x1 - x4)]\n      = [(x - 0)(x - 3)(x - 4)(x - 7)] / [(1 - 0)(1 - 3)(1 - 4)(1 - 7)]\n\nl2(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x3)(x - x4)] / [(x2 - x0)(x2 - x1)(x2 - x3)(x2 - x4)]\n      = [(x - 0)(x - 1)(x - 4)(x - 7)] / [(3 - 0)(3 - 1)(3 - 4)(3 - 7)]\n\nl3(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x2)(x - x4)] / [(x3 - x0)(x3 - x1)(x3 - x2)(x3 - x4)]\n      = [(x - 0)(x - 1)(x - 3)(x - 7)] / [(4 - 0)(4 - 1)(4 - 3)(4 - 7)]\n\nl4(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x2)(x - x3)] / [(x4 - x0)(x4 - x1)(x4 - x2)(x4 - x3)]\n      = [(x - 0)(x - 1)(x - 3)(x - 4)] / [(7 - 0)(7 - 1)(7 - 3)(7 - 4)]\n\nNow, let's find the approximation for f(2) and f(5).\n\nFor f(2):\n\nL(2) = l0(2) * f(x0) + l1(2) * f(x1) + l2(2) * f(x2) + l3(2) * f(x3) + l4(2) * f(x4)\n     = [(2 - 1)(2 - 3)(2 - 4)(2 - 7)] / [(0 - 1)(0 - 3)(0 - 4)(0 - 7)] * 2.2\n       + [(2 - 0)(2 - 3)(2 - 4)(2 - 7)] / [(1 - 0)(1 - 3)(1 - 4)(1 - 7)] * 6.7\n       + [(2 - 0)(2 - 1)(2 - 4)(2 - 7)] / [(3 - 0)(3 - 1)(3 - 4)(3 - 7)] * 1.6\n       + [(2 - 0)(2 - 1)(2 - 3)(2 - 7)] / [(4 - 0)(4 - 1)(4 - 3)(4 - 7)] * 8.1\n       + [(2 - 0)(2 - 1)(2 - 3)(2 - 4)] / [(7 - 0)(7 - 1)(7 - 3)(7 - 4)] * 3.9\n     ≈ 4.96\n\nFor f(5):\n\nL(5) = l0(5) * f(x0) + l1(5) * f(x1) + l2(5) * f(x2) + l3(5) * f(x3) + l4(5) * f(x4)\n     = [(5 - 1)(5 - 3)(5 - 4)(5 - 7)] / [(0 - 1)(0 - 3)(0 - 4)(0 - 7)] * 2.2\n       + [(5 - 0)(5 - 3)(5 - 4)(5 - 7)] / [(1 - 0)(1 - 3)(1 - 4)(1 - 7)] * 6.7\n       + [(5 - 0)(5 - 1)(5 - 4)(5 - 7)] / [(3 - 0)(3 - 1)(3 - 4)(3 - 7)] * 1.6\n       + [(5 - 0)(5 - 1)(5 - 3)(5 - 7)] / [(4 - 0)(4 - 1)(4 - 3)(4 - 7)] * 8.1\n       + [(5 - 0)(5 - 1)(5 - 3)(5 - 4)] / [(7 - 0)(7 - 1)(7 - 3)(7 - 4)] * 3.9\n     ≈ 6.04\n\nSo, the approximations for f(2) and f(5) using Lagrange polynomials are 4.96 and 6.04, respectively."
